# {{ docset_name }} Docset Generator

Generate a [Dash](https://kapeli.com/dash) docset for [{{ docset_name }} documentation]({{ docs_url }}).

## Features

- Scrapes all documentation from {{ docs_domain }}
- Creates a properly indexed Dash docset with semantic search
- Indexes API references, guides, and more
- Supports offline documentation browsing

## Requirements

- Python 3.12+
- [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/getting-started/installation/) - fast Python package manager

## Installation

```bash
# Install uv if you haven't already
curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh

# Clone the repository
git clone <repo-url>
cd {{ project_name }}

# Install dependencies
uv sync

# Install pre-commit hooks
prek install
```

## Usage

### Quick Start (with poe)

```bash
poe scrape    # Scrape docs and build docset
poe verify    # Validate the docset
poe all       # Scrape + verify
poe rebuild   # Clean + scrape + verify
poe clean     # Remove output/ and .cache/
poe check     # Run type checker
```

### Manual Commands

```bash
# Scrape docs from {{ docs_domain }} and build docset
uv run main.py --scrape

# Build from existing scraped docs
uv run main.py --source .cache/{{ docset_identifier }}-docs

# Validate the docset
uv run verify.py -v
```

## Output

The generated docset will be at `output/{{ docset_name }}.docset`.

To install in Dash:
1. Open Dash
2. Go to Preferences > Docsets
3. Click + and select the `.docset` file

Or simply double-click the `.docset` file.

